# Styling

## Official docs

- [CSS](https://nextjs.org/docs/app/getting-started/css) — global, CSS Modules, Tailwind, external packages
- [Tailwind CSS v3](https://nextjs.org/docs/app/guides/tailwind-v3-css)
- [Sass](https://nextjs.org/docs/app/guides/sass)
- [CSS-in-JS](https://nextjs.org/docs/app/guides/css-in-js) (compatibility notes)
- Config: [cssChunking](https://nextjs.org/docs/app/api-reference/config/next-config-js/cssChunking), [inlineCss](https://nextjs.org/docs/app/api-reference/config/next-config-js/inlineCss)

## Checklist

- [ ] Prefer colocation and CSS Modules or design-system patterns consistent with the repo.
- [ ] **Tailwind v3** doc path if you need broader browser support per [Tailwind v3 guide](https://nextjs.org/docs/app/guides/tailwind-v3-css); **v4** may use different setup — follow current Next + Tailwind release notes.
- [ ] Third-party component CSS: see [Package bundling](https://nextjs.org/docs/app/guides/package-bundling) if tree-shaking or side effects are an issue.

